node.text:
A big motivator of mine has always been to try and pay it forward, and with that said, I'm proud to announce the launch of the @ryandungeyfoundation . Our goal is to focus our efforts on supporting the fight against childhood cancer and our commitment to help children live healthy and active lifestyles. 

In 2012, I partnered with @stjude to create a benefit cycling event known as the MN Major River-to-River ride, which eventually evolved to the St. Jude Ride and 5K Run. Together, with all of your support, we raised more than 1.2 million dollars for the cause. The Ryan Dungey Foundation will allow for even greater involvement and more fundraising opportunities with St. Jude as well as supporting @allkidsbike who are on a mission to get kids on two wheels.

I genuinely appreciate everyone's support!

-RD

node.text:
After careful consideration and a lot of thought, I am excited to share an update to our 2020 @stjuderiderunmn event.
.
I hope you will join us for our first ever VIRTUAL St. Jude Ride and 5k Run on Sunday, July 19, 2020.  Registration is $30 for the virtual ride or 5K — kids ride/run for free!
.
Even though we will not be riding, running or walking together at Afton Apple Orchard, I can't wait to virtually connect and celebrate everything you all continue to do ensuring our lifesaving work for @stjude continues.
.
In moments that separate us, we unite as one. Because together, nothing is impossible. Register today.
.
@stjuderiderunmn @stjude @stjudetwincities @anderson_races

node.title: 2020 St Jude Ride & 5K Run- Event Update

node.text:
A big motivator of mine has always been to try and pay it forward, and with that said, I'm proud to announce the launch of the @ryandungeyfoundation . Our goal is to focus our efforts on supporting the fight against childhood cancer and our commitment to help children live healthy and active lifestyles. 

In 2012, I partnered with @stjude to create a benefit cycling event known as the MN Major River-to-River ride, which eventually evolved to the St. Jude Ride and 5K Run. Together, with all of your support, we raised more than 1.2 million dollars for the cause. The Ryan Dungey Foundation will allow for even greater involvement and more fundraising opportunities with St. Jude as well as supporting @allkidsbike who are on a mission to get kids on two wheels.

I genuinely appreciate everyone's support!

-RD

Washougal was a track I always enjoyed going back to every year. The track and dirt really suited my riding style and things came a little more natural to me there. Plus this is where I got my very first outdoor overall so it was very special! 
Here is a real from my last win to my first.

node.text:
The 2011 @ProMotocross Southwick National was stressful while in the midst of a championship title fight. I managed to get the first moto win, but had to join Moto 2 about 3/4 of a lap down due to an electrical issue. It's never easy to stay calm in those situations, and if that day taught me anything, it was the importance to never give up and make the most out of your bad days as I managed to lose just a single point. 

I go in depth about the day on this weeks @RD_Coffee Thursday Coffee episode .

node.text:
Through my relationship with Nike I was able to express my interest in becoming a @livestrong ambassador during the 2009 season, hoping to begin my own philanthropic journey. I met @lancearmstrong at his Hope Rides Again event in Los Angeles and felt extremely fortunate to be recognized by Livestrong as an athlete ambassador they believed could help broaden their awareness with a new audience. We decided the 2009 RedBud National was the perfect fit for my introduction as a Livestrong ambassador. 

Read my latest Moto Memories blog on RDCoffees.com
